value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins in the presynaptic actin cytoskeleton.
The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a presynapse.
Cell-cell signaling in which the ligand is carried between cells by an exosome.
Transynaptic signaling in which the ligand is carried across the synapse by an exosome.

label.value: postsynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the postsynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.

label.value: presynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the presynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a presynapse.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a postsynapse.
Any process that modulates the physical form of a presynapse.
Any process that modulates the physical form of a postsynapse.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of trans-synaptic signaling.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures and their associated proteins in the presynaptic cytoskeleton.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising cytoskeletal filaments and their associated proteins in the postsynaptic cytoskeleton.
Fusion of the membrane of a vesicle with the plasma membrane, thereby releasing its contents into the extracellular space.
The lipid bilayer surrounding an exocytic vesicle.
A cytoplasmic, membrane bound vesicle that is capable of fusing to the plasma membrane to release its contents into the extracellular space.
A polymer consisting of an indefinite number of protein or protein complex subunits that have polymerised to form a fiber-shaped structure.
A component of the cytoskeleton consisting of a homo or heteropolymeric fiber constructed from an indeterminate number of protein subunits.
The transport of organelles or other particles from one location in the cell to another along actin filaments.
The directed movement of a vesicle along a cytoskeletal fiber such as a microtubule or and actin filament, mediated by motor proteins.

label.value: presynaptic process involved in chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: The pathway leading to secretion of a neurotransmitter from the presynapse as part of synaptic transmission.
Cell-cell signaling to, from or within a synapse.
Cell-cell signaling in either direction across the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling to or from a synapse, mediated by a peptide.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by a peptide ligand crossing the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling from post to pre-synapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a lipid.

label.value: regulation of translation at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, across the synaptic cleft, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the vesicular release and reception of neuropeptide molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by lipid, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the release and reception of lipid molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Any (proper) part of the cytoplasm of a single cell of sufficient size to still be considered cytoplasm.
The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the presynapse.
The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the postsynapse.

label.value: regulation of translation at presynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: A process in which protein is transported from one region of the plasma membrane to another.
The directed movement of proteins along microtubules in neuron projections.
Any signal release from a synapse.
The complete extent of cell cortex that underlies some some region of the plasma membrane.

label.value: regulation of skeletal muscle contraction by action potential

value.value: Any action potential process that regulates skeletal muscle contraction.
The multiplication or reproduction of blood vessel endothelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.
A mitotic cell cycle process which results in the assembly, arrangement, or disassembly of the nuclear inner or outer membrane during mitosis.

definition.value: This process only occurs in organisms which undergo 'closed mitosis' without nuclear breakdown.

value.value: The process in which a nuclear membrane is synthesized, aggregates, and bonds together.
Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an environmental stimulus.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a prolongation or process extending from a neuron, e.g. an axon, or a dendrite.

label.value: regulation of cellular response to osmotic stress

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cellular response to osmotic stress.

label.value: regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus.

label.value: negative regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fustion with Golgi apparatus.

label.value: positive regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly, disassembly or arrangement of constituent parts of the basement membrane.
